manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Speed Ahead with USB 3.2 Gen2 x2 The SD810 supports the USB 3.2 Gen2 x2 high-speed transmission specification, with read/write speeds of up to 2000MB/s. This drive meets the high-speed access requirements of video creators or expert photographers.

Lightweight and Durable The SD810 utilizes a high-quality aluminum alloy case to improve heat dissipation and maintain stable transfer speeds even under continuous load. It is lightweight and easy to carry and can be used anytime anywhere.

A Powerful Shield for Critical Data The SD810 has passed the strict IP68 standard for water resistance and dust resistance. The drive is nearly impervious to dust ingress and can be immersed in water greater than 1 meter for up to 60 minutes. The SD810 has excellent waterproof, dustproof, and drop-proof capabilities.

Military-Grade for All Your Challenges SD810 also meets the MIL-STD-810G 516.6 impact resistance standard to easily survive accidental drops and jarring. This protection shields your files, giving you peace of mind when transferring files while frequenting the outdoors.

Your Game Library The SD810 can be connected to the latest generation of game consoles. Games that do not fit on the consoles' internal storage can be stored in the SD810. The drive is making it easy to expand your game library and add to your entertainment lifestyle.
Hassle-Free Compatibility Whether Android, macOS, Windows, or other operating systems, you will not need to worry about compatibility. Just connect via its Type-C port and go.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great drive, but provided cables did not work
reviews.reviewText: This drive is pretty cool when it comes to speed (my max was ~1GB/s) and the physical footprint of the drive being pretty small. I would have given this drive a five-star rating except one thing; using this drive initially was a pain... my device did not recognize the SSD, and I was unable to find it using the disk manager through Windows 10. After fiddling with the cable the drive was finally recognizable but was not able to transfer any data. I then tried another Type c to USB cable and the drive worked perfectly. With this said, the two cables that are provided in the Box (a type c to type c and a type c to USB A) are able to transmit power to the SSD but not able to transfer any data (Windows 10 prompting with an error when trying to load the drive). This was not much of a problem for myself because I have extra cables lying around. For the average user however, having these two provided cables not work properly can be of an inconvenience and lead to them buying a separate cable. Aside from the cables not working properly, like I mentioned above, the drive is very fast and I am able to game off it. While using the SSD it does get warm but this is normal. After moving a lot of data it does get pretty hot to touch but cools off rather quickly. It is best to leave the drive exposed to the open air when using it and not have it under anything or surrounded by other objects. Overall this is a great drive. I would say this is great for the money however I bought this when it was on sale, and it was a great buy at the sale price. For the non-sale price however, it can be a little expensive when compared to competitors like Samsung, but when compared to brand named gaming SSDs, this is a great alternative.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worth the money/erase and partition needed
reviews.reviewText: My Mac was very slow and not shutting down and I bought it as a startup SSD. This is not plug-and-play. It needs configuration. I am no expert and had a few days of struggle. I find it very confusing that Q&A says will not work for Mac and says described in the ad. It is wrong. This SSD works. The start time gets much faster from 10-15 minutes to 1-2 minutes. This is good enough for me. Disk speed is advertised up to 1000 mb/s; actual 550-850 write, 850 read. It has frozen a few times. I do not know how long this SSD lasts.Overall it is fast. It solved many of my problems.To install, there are several steps you need to be careful. I followed Apple community and MacWorld review, both lack some details. The manual did not help me how to partition the disk, but I recommend to read the manual for the rest. I have to go back to the Apple community to partition. My memory is somewhat vague but here is what I did:1. Connect it to the computer. Icon showed up and could be opened (but I could not save a file).2. Go to Disk Utility and format SSD with GUID. Specifics are in step 3 next. A few key points:- Make sure you are looking at DIsk. My default was to show "volume" and I format it and gave me an error, "the disk is locked." I had to change the setting to view the Disk and Volume in the Disk Utility. Then I format it and it worked.3. In the Disk Utility, click "Erase (this is "formatting" and the term was confusing). Type:- Name: You name the disk you want- Format: macOS Extended (Journaled)- Partition: GUIDName, Format and Partition show up at the same time. If you are looking at Volume, partition would not show up. Make sure you are "erasing (formatting)" the Disk but not the Volume. I did not notice I was looking at the volume and I was so frustrated that the partition did not allow me to choose GUID. I had to repeat the step several times to figure it out.4. Press "OK" or could be "Apply." Do not remember.5. After finishing formatting, install macOS or restore using Time Machine. You can do it by pressing "command+R" when starting the Mac. The choice should show up.6. When starting, press "option" and choose your SSD.7. Mac should start up from your SSD.From my experience, I would recommend a faster connection Thunderbolt 3 or USB-C. My WB disk has 4tb with usb; I think it is usb3.0 that looks rectangular. It is extremely slow. I went for ~1000 MB/s over 500 MB/s because I worried about the speed. You could go over 2000 MB/s if you choose Thunderbolt 3.
Super facil de operar y con una velocidad increible.

reviews.reviewTitle: Work straight out of the box.
reviews.reviewText: Got SSD for backup storage and gaming. Compact; it disappear in my hand folded. Easy peazy, worked straight out the box. So far no major issues. This device has blazing speed which does bring up the warmth a bit; but that's manageable. Only issue I have is the ~ 1TB is too small; should have gotten the ~2TB.
It is fast, and small so it is easy to place around computer area. Only small downside is that the cord is about 1 foot long so there isn't much option as to where you can place it after connecting

For me this is a very good product . The one I got is 512 gigs and is very compact and has a metal casing with a cover on one side that protects it from dust and water which is a good thing, seems to be very durable, it's a very good buy!I use it mostly to back up video clips pictures and other files, works great. The dimensions are:1"3/4 by 3" by 3/8" And weighs 39 gram, very compact.
